21/07/2004
PORTOROZ, Slovenia -- Croatian and Slovenian border police services started joint patrols Tuesday (20 July), in line with a bilateral agreement. The police departments of Koper, Slovenia and Istria, Croatia announced the news at a joint press conference. The heads of the two departments said co-operation between the two countries' services will help the fight against cross-border crime and illegal migration. There were 222 illegal border crossing cases in the first half of this year, five less compared to the same period in 2003. (HINA, STA - 20/07/04)
